The GSMA has released its The Mobile Economy 2017 report for Sub-Saharan Africa. The report states that 3G connectivity is almost universal in South Africa, while 4G networks now reach 75% of the population. Consequently, the country has a mobile penetration rate of almost 70%, said the GSMA. The report stated that South Africa has a unique mobile penetration rate of 68%, with 37.5 million unique mobile subscribers in the country. It further stated that IP messaging has shown strong growth in the country, with 90% of users in South Africa using at least one IP messaging service regularly. This includes the likes ofÂ WhatsApp, BBM, and Facebook Messenger.